      "seed": 2037832669,
      "version": 1355,
      "versionNonce": 513934799,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776138549619,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- Agentic Knowledge Work — why I am doing this video\n  https://lawrencewu.net/posts/2026-03-04-agentic-knowledge-work/\n\n- My Journey\n    - Data Scientist for 10+ years - data analytics, machine learning, training ML models\n        - Tools: R, Python, RStudio (dplyr, tidyverse), SQL, Jupyter, sklearn, pytorch, pandas, streamlit, StackOverflow\n    - November 2022-Dec 2023 - ChatGPT moment, LangChain, Prompt Engineering, Github Copilot\n    - 2024 - LangGraph, Cursor\n    - 2025 - Year of Claude Code\n        - March - First heard about Claude Code, thought it was \"yet another agent framework\"\n        - July - Started to use it: https://lawrencewu.net/posts/2025-07-18-starting-to-use-claude-code/\n        - February - Looking back 2025 was the year of Claude Code. It's a tool that is unlike any other tool I've used.\n    - 2026\n        - January - Claude Cowork - so much latent demand, they put a UI around Claude Code\n        - February - Karpathy's Autoresearch",
      "fontSize": 19.836197916666684,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- Agentic Knowledge Work — why I am doing this video\n  https://lawrencewu.net/posts/2026-03-04-agentic-knowledge-work/\n\n- My Journey\n    - Data Scientist for 10+ years - data analytics, machine learning, training ML models\n        - Tools: R, Python, RStudio (dplyr, tidyverse), SQL, Jupyter, sklearn, pytorch, pandas, streamlit, StackOverflow\n    - November 2022-Dec 2023 - ChatGPT moment, LangChain, Prompt Engineering, Github Copilot\n    - 2024 - LangGraph, Cursor\n    - 2025 - Year of Claude Code\n        - March - First heard about Claude Code, thought it was \"yet another agent framework\"\n        - July - Started to use it: https://lawrencewu.net/posts/2025-07-18-starting-to-use-claude-code/\n        - February - Looking back 2025 was the year of Claude Code. It's a tool that is unlike any other tool I've used.\n    - 2026\n        - January - Claude Cowork - so much latent demand, they put a UI around Claude Code\n        - February - Karpathy's Autoresearch",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
