    {
      "id": "pDaZNQlvU5-Ai4ofpmMTN",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -945.0611568186544,
      "y": 1339.3249655857012,
      "width": 1477.6352864734622,
      "height": 428.4618750000004,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b22",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 735784960,
      "version": 2676,
      "versionNonce": 759683533,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775000370746,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- Going from no AI-usage to using something like ChatGPT. Many people have replaced Google with ChatGPT. But through this lesson I want to make a case for why\ncoding agents are another step change in usefulness.\n- When to use CC vs ChatGPT: ChatGPT is good for Q&A, coding agents are good for knowledge work\n- Every person has a different skillset and experience. Coding agents let you go way deeper in\n    your area and broader into adjacent areas.\n- Case Study: me as a Data Scientist --> me as a Data Scientist (Deeper) + Data Engineer + Project Manager + Python tooling builder\n        Deeper: training transformer models, finetuning for different tasks, scaling training on GPUs using VertexAI Pipelines (GCP's wrapper around Kubeflow)\n        Broader: Data Engineer - Given access to the raw data, I can build my own da ta pipelines and engineer my own features\n                        ML Engineer - I can experiment with different deployment patterns\n                        Project Manager - I can use an agent to manage my tasks and help me do planning\n                        Other tooling\n                            - build re-usable Python tooling with libraries, templates\n                            - Github Actions - automate much work and review, create composite actions (things I'm not really that familiar with)\n                            - Build and maintain LLM Gateways like LiteLLM\n                            - Skills marketplaces \n                                    all this that makes me and others more productive...",
      "fontSize": 19.836197916666684,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- Going from no AI-usage to using something like ChatGPT. Many people have replaced Google with ChatGPT. But through this lesson I want to make a case for why coding agents are another step change in usefulness.\n- When to use CC vs ChatGPT: ChatGPT is good for Q&A, coding agents are good for knowledge work\n- Every person has a different skillset and experience. Coding agents let you go way deeper in\n    your area and broader into adjacent areas.\n- Case Study: me as a Data Scientist --> me as a Data Scientist (Deeper) + Data Engineer + Project Manager + Python tooling builder\n        Deeper: training transformer models, finetuning for different tasks, scaling training on GPUs using VertexAI Pipelines (GCP's wrapper around Kubeflow)\n        Broader: Data Engineer - Given access to the raw data, I can build my own da ta pipelines and engineer my own features\n                        ML Engineer - I can experiment with different deployment patterns\n                        Project Manager - I can use an agent to manage my tasks and help me do planning\n                        Other tooling\n                            - build re-usable Python tooling with libraries, templates\n                            - Github Actions - automate much work and review, create composite actions (things I'm not really that familiar with)\n                            - Build and maintain LLM Gateways like LiteLLM\n                            - Skills marketplaces \n                                    all this that makes me and others more productive...",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
    {
      "id": "sOczjjOzKVPAXmt-qAZtL",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -928.6532630821995,
      "y": 1283.005895574754,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 30,
      "angle": 0,
